        "client_msg_id": "56cc768a-d723-4ef0-8c32-0101d0bf1f2e",
        "text": "since we were talking about use cases, this piece of <@U02QC0PPER3>'s writeup stands out to me\n<https:\/\/model-view-self-modify.netlify.app\/readme>\n&gt; Most important to me, it'd spread the subversive ideas that code _is_ data _is_ code, that \"using\" _is_ \"programming\", that any UI forms a [weak] language, and that tools should be moldable.\nthe event sourcing pattern is useful simply to record the practice of an experienced editor - either oneself, or a more senior practitioner, usually\n\nas Beni points out, chess folks use algebraic notation to reflect on their practice regularly",
