        "text": "moldable tools make skillful practice _feel_ easy. at the same time, I've never, ever seen beginners pick them up. and I've taught plenty of beginners who struggled with the excess degrees of freedom.\n\none key exception here might be Shiffman's Nature of Code; I encountered his tutorials through the in-editor Processing examples, which are great. (now he's got a fun and easy-to-read deepdive on flocking: <https:\/\/natureofcode.com\/autonomous-agents\/>",
